On this 13-point scale, the cervix is scored on a scale from 0-3 on consistency, position, dilation, effacement, and station of the fetal presenting part. A higher Bishop score indicates an increased likelihood of successful induction that results in vaginal birth. For nulliparous women, a score 26-8 usually indicates that induction will be successful
